// @test regression/INV106-function-body-if-return-types
// @description A function whose implicit RETURN is a trailing if-statement with incompatible branch types (42 vs "no") is TV's CE10235 - the same branch-compatibility rule as an if/switch EXPRESSION, but `if` in return position parses as an IfStatement, which the expression path never reached. A function returning compatible branches stays clean. Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV106.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Return type of one of the "if" or "switch" blocks is not compatible/
// @expects errors: 1

//@version=6
indicator("INV106-function-body-if-return-types")
f(c) =>
    if c
        42
    else
        "no"
g(c) =>
    if c
        1
    else
        2
x = f(true)
y = g(true)
plot(y)
